<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🧱 M000 Week 2 — English Worksheet (Intermediate)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Placing Blocks · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Level:</strong> Intermediate · <strong>Time:</strong> about 38 minutes</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each set of steps. Before you imagine the agent doing it, write what you think will happen.</p>
<pre><code>place block down
move forward
place block down
move forward
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>How many blocks did the agent place, and what shape do they make?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>move up by 1
place block down
move up by 1
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Are these blocks in a line on the ground, or stacked? Write one sentence saying how you know.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place block down
turn right
move forward
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Where is the second block compared to the first one? Explain.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Each block of code below is broken. You are told the goal first, then a hint about where to look. Read the code, then rewrite it so it works. After that, write one sentence explaining what was wrong.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — Goal: place a block, move forward, then place another block.
Hint: look at the very first line — is the agent placing before it moves?</p>
<pre><code>move forward
place block down
move forward
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What was wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — Goal: place a row of 3 blocks in a straight line.
Hint: the agent never moves, so the blocks all land in the same spot.</p>
<pre><code>place block down
place block down
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What was wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — Goal: place 2 blocks stacked on top of each other.
Hint: <code>move forward</code> and <code>move up by 1</code> do not do the same thing.</p>
<pre><code>place block down
move forward
place block down
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What was wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now switch to your homework world. Place <strong>4 blocks</strong> — make some in a line and some stacked, so your build has more than one shape. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of what you placed, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 3 or 4 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>First, I used the command … to place the block.</p>
<p>Then I moved … so the next block would land …</p>
<p>To make the blocks stack, I …</p>
<p>The hardest part was …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Now take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you walk the camera through your world. Talk through it like you are teaching someone who has never seen it. Try to use these words: <strong>place</strong>, <strong>block</strong>, <strong>move</strong>, <strong>forward</strong>, <strong>up</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show the blocks you placed.</li>
<li>Read your commands out loud and say what each one does.</li>
<li>Point out where the blocks are stacked and explain how you did it.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> Plan it here before you record — you can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
